    "analysis": "Metric analysis on the five candidate services found only two anomaly runs: ts-auth-service:error and ts-order-service:error. Both runs show global_p95=0.0 and window values equal to 0.0 for the whole incident window (25 points), which is likely a false-positive pattern because the KPI never deviates above 0 (threshold equals values). Therefore metrics did not surface a clear resource fault (CPU/mem/disk/socket) among the candidate services. According to the workflow, we should next use traces to localize the root-cause service among candidate services (especially when multiple services show ambiguous metric signals). Trace features like per-service error_rate or downstream duration increases can identify the most downstream faulty service. I will ask the Executor to scan trace telemetry for trace features that mention any of the five candidate services and report their global thresholds and exceedances inside the incident window.",
